<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-BJUC2Tlxc0ypCg5I3yZZHw" name="new_toolmentor,_vR2_ACIPEd2A-8dHkHQC-g" guid="-BJUC2Tlxc0ypCg5I3yZZHw" changeDate="2008-09-24T09:44:33.500-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; RequisitePro&amp;reg;&lt;/strong> helps you to store the project's requirements. To initialize your&#xD;
    requirement repository, RequisitePro provides you with various project templates, such as RUP template, Use Case&#xD;
    Template, Traditional Template.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>To create a new requirement and assign attributes to a requirement:&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Select &lt;strong>File &amp;gt;&lt;/strong> &lt;strong>New &amp;gt; Requirement&lt;/strong>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The New Requirement Properties box is displayed&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Fill in the following information in the &lt;strong>General&lt;/strong> tab &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Type&lt;/strong>: Select the proper type from the &lt;b>Requirement Type&lt;/b> drop-down list&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Name&lt;/strong>: Type the short name of the requirement&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Description&lt;/strong>: Type the description of the requirement&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Package&lt;/strong>: Select the proper package by clicking the &lt;strong>Browse&lt;/strong> button&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Select the &lt;strong>Attributes&lt;/strong> tab to fill in the following information&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Priority&lt;/strong>: Select the proper priority from the drop-down list, for which the possible&#xD;
                values are Low, Medium, or High&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Status&lt;/strong>: Select the proper status (Proposed, Approved, Incorporated, or Validation)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Difficulty&lt;/strong>: Select the proper difficulty level (Low, Medium, or High)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Stability&lt;/strong>: Select the proper stability value (Low, Medium, or High)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Assigned To&lt;/strong>: Type the name of the person who is responsible for this requirement&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Origin&lt;/strong>: Select the proper origin value (Customers, Development, or Executive Committee)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Obsolete&lt;/strong>: Select the proper status (Yes or No)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    See also Rational RequisitePro online &lt;strong>Help &amp;gt; Contents and Index &amp;gt;Assigning values to requirement&#xD;
    attributes&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Note:&lt;/strong> If the attribute type or requirement type is not available in your project template, you can add&#xD;
    them by doing the following:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Select &lt;strong>File &amp;gt; Project Administration &amp;gt; Properties&lt;/strong>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The New Requirement Properties box is displayed&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Do the following information in the &lt;strong>Requirement Type&lt;/strong> or &lt;strong>Attributes&lt;/strong> tab:&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click &lt;b>Add&lt;/b> to add a new type&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Fill in all necessary information and click &lt;b>OK&lt;/b>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    With the initial version of requirement, the version number in the &lt;b>Revision&lt;/b> tab will automatically start at&#xD;
    1.0001&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></mainDescription>
